\begin_layout Section
Introduction
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Football Match Result Database (FMRD) stores and maintains the match
 result data needed to support football (soccer) research activities for
 the benefit of the football analytics community.
 The current version of the database handles domestic league competitions.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Football Match Result Database does the following:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Maintain data on matches that occur within football league competitions,
 whether among national teams or domestic clubs.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Maintain complete top-level information on the football match, including
 match date, competition name and stage, participating teams, venues, and
 environmental conditions.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Maintain complete information on macro-events that occur during a match,
 including goals, penalties, disciplinary incidents, and substitutions.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Maintain complete information on participating personnel, such as players,
 managers, and match referees.
\end_layout

